  "doc_id": "48437",
  "text": "Topoisomerase II (topo II) is a ubiquitous enzyme that is able to transiently break a DNA duplex and transport another DNA duplex through the break in an ATP-dependent manner. Topo II thereby contributes to unlinking DNA during replication, and is required for chromosome condensation and segregation at mitosis [CITATION_1] .",
